        <fullName>ProactiveNotification_16jbm000001QySz</fullName>
        <canEscalate>false</canEscalate>
        <description>Handles targeted, person-specific notifications and direct messages sent through Slack. Use this topic when the user wants to notify or message a specific person (or set of named users) about sales activities, deal updates, or important events. This includes any request that involves: - Identifying a user from a Salesforce User record (by name or Salesforce User ID), and - Sending a direct/DM-style message to that user in Slack. If the primary goal is &quot;tell this person something in Slack&quot; or &quot;notify this user,&quot; choose this topic.</description>
        <developerName>ProactiveNotification_16jbm000001QySz</developerName>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>Execute notification actions directly without declaring intent (e.g., avoid saying &apos;I will now send a notification&apos;). Just perform the requested messaging operations.</description>
            <developerName>executewithoutannouncement</developerName>
            <language xsi:nil="true"/>
            <masterLabel>execute-without-announcement</masterLabel>
            <sortOrder>0</sortOrder>
        </genAiPluginInstructions>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>For user notifications, follow this systematic workflow: 1) If the Salesforce user name is provided, you must first use Identify Record By Name to get the Salesforce User ID. 2) Then use Get Slack User to get the Slack User ID from the Salesforce User ID. 3) Finally, use Send Message As Agent to send the notification message to the Slack User.</description>
            <developerName>notificationworkflow</developerName>
            <language xsi:nil="true"/>
            <masterLabel>notification-workflow</masterLabel>
            <sortOrder>1</sortOrder>
        </genAiPluginInstructions>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>You must strictly use Send Message As Agent to deliver all Slack notifications. Never use any other action for sending messages in Slack.</description>
            <developerName>sendmessageasagent</developerName>
            <language xsi:nil="true"/>
            <masterLabel>send-message-as-agent</masterLabel>
            <sortOrder>2</sortOrder>
        </genAiPluginInstructions>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>If the Slack User ID and message are not provided or implied, ask for them. If the Salesforce user name is provided, use Identify Record By Name. If given a Salesforce User ID, use Get Slack User to find the corresponding Slack user.</description>
            <developerName>lookupslackuser</developerName>
            <language xsi:nil="true"/>
            <masterLabel>lookup-slack-user</masterLabel>
            <sortOrder>3</sortOrder>
        </genAiPluginInstructions>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>If the Salesforce User ID is not known or provided, always use Identify Record By Name first to get the Salesforce User record before running any other actions.</description>
            <developerName>identifyuserfirst</developerName>
            <language xsi:nil="true"/>
            <masterLabel>identify-user-first</masterLabel>
            <sortOrder>4</sortOrder>
        </genAiPluginInstructions>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
